137007,variable,BONTRoyalAssassinRollerWheelUV,,Bont Royal Assassin Indoor UV Roller Skate Wheels,1,0,visible,Unleash Your Skating Potential with the Bont Royal Assassin Wheels,"Royal Assassin Indoor UV Skate Wheels - High -Performance Skating

\nThe Royal Assassin Indoor UV Wheel puts everything skaters adore about our legendary urethane into a blaze of light. Ideal for indoor speed skating, derby, jam, and session skating, these wheels absorb light to glow in the dark and radiate brightly under UV blacklight. Coming in various sizes, they offer high-performance racing technology blended with a visual spectacular that turns every session into a night to remember.

\n

Glows under blacklight or in the dark
\nRecharges with sunlight or artificial light, glowing up to 30 minutes per charge
\nGravity-poured Corey urethane provides incredible rebound, grip, and durability
\nAircraft-grade 6061 aluminum hub produces responsiveness, precision, and strength
\nUnique groove design breaks-in instantly, no break-in time needed

\nUnlike typical mass-produced wheels, the Royal Assassin Indoor UV Wheel uses a premium urethane formula crafted by renowned urethane expert Scott Corey. This advanced formula delivers unmatched rebound, superior grip, and long-lasting durability, giving skaters a competitive edge with every push.

\nEvery wheel is gravity-poured to ensure uniform density and avoid imperfections common in injection-molded wheels. The end result is a smoother, faster, and more predictable ride from your very first run.

\nWhat makes this UV edition different are the UV-reactive particles infused in the urethane. Leave the wheels out under the sun or in any spotlight, and they radiate for around 30 minutes. In rink blacklights, the effect is even stronger, giving it a truly breathtaking appearance that adds to every skating experience. This wheel optimizes performance and appearance, making every session a thrilling one as much as it is competitive.

\nThe 6061 aircraft-grade aluminum hub is designed for strength and precision, providing a smooth bearing seat to optimize roll efficiency and power transfer. 137548,variable,BONTRoyalAssassinRollerWheels-1,,BONT Royal Assassin Indoor Roller Skate Wheels,1,0,visible,Unleash Your Skating Potential with the Bont Royal Assassin Wheels,"

Royal Assassin – 59 × 38 mm Roller Derby Wheel

\n

Ready to level up your roller derby game? The Bont Royal Assassin Wheel is built for skaters who want speed, control, and confidence on every turn. Designed with precision and made from top-grade urethane, this wheel brings a perfect mix of smooth roll and powerful grip.

\n

Smooth, Grippy, and Fast

\n

With a 92A hardness rating, the Royal Assassin is a little softer than most derby wheels. That softness gives you better traction on indoor tracks — whether you’re skating on polished concrete, wood, or sport court. You’ll feel a silky roll that lets you glide through corners, stop fast, and accelerate out of turns without losing balance. No more guessing which wheels will work — this one just performs.

\n

Built to Last

\n

These wheels aren’t just fast — they’re tough. The Royal Assassin is known for lasting twice as long as most derby wheels, even under the pressure of daily training and competition. You get consistent performance, less wear, and great value for your money.

\n

Loved by Skaters Everywhere

\n

Thousands of roller derby skaters around the world trust the Royal Assassin. From local leagues to professional competitors, this wheel has become a favorite because it delivers what skaters really want: reliability, control, and that perfect feel on the track.

\n

Made for Every Style

\n

Blockers love the solid grip and stability. Jammers love the quick response and light feel. However you skate, these wheels help you stay fast, focused, and ready for action. Pair them with your favorite Bont derby boots and plates for a setup that moves like an extension of you.

\n

Size: 59 mm × 38 mm

\n

Surface: Indoor derby floors

\n

Material: High-rebound premium urethane

\n

Core: Lightweight reinforced hub

\n

Why You’ll Love Them

\n

Strong grip and smooth roll on almost any indoor surface

\n

Longer-lasting than most wheels in its class

\n

Trusted by pros and loved by everyday derby skaters

\n

Consistent, reliable performance from the first jam to the last

\n

The Bottom Line

\n

If you’re ready for a wheel that works as hard as you do, the Bont Royal Assassin is your perfect match. Smooth, durable, and competition-ready — these wheels help you skate faster, hit harder, and feel more connected to the track.

Embrace the Uniqueness: Handcrafted Bont Royal Assassin Wheels

Our commitment to crafting high-performance wheels by hand means that each Bont Royal Assassin wheel is a unique creation, shaped by artistry and the nature of our premium urethane. While we strive for excellence, the handmade process and materials can result in subtle variations that add character and authenticity to your wheels.
Here are a few natural occurrences you might expect:

column2: • Air Bubbles Our high-performance urethane may contain tiny air bubbles, a natural part of the manufacturing process. These are harmless and won't affect performance. We have specific criteria to ensure these bubbles are minimal:
• Skate surface: Up to 3 bubbles, each 3mm or smaller, not grouped together.
• Wheel Face and Lip: Up to 2 bubbles, each 2mm or smaller, not grouped together.
• Back of the wheel: Up to 2 bubbles, each 4mm or smaller, not grouped together.

column1: Streaks The face of the wheel may exhibit subtle streaks, adding a unique visual touch.
Slight Hub Scratches Before pouring the urethane, the hub is prepared through sandblasting and priming. A clamp during this process can sometimes leave a tiny imperfection on the hub.
Grooves We hand-buff the grooves in each wheel, ensuring a faster break-in period. This personal touch means each wheel will be slightly different, showcasing the artistry of the final buff.

These natural variations are not defects; they are a testament to the handcrafted nature of your Bont Royal Assassin wheels. They add to the charm and individuality of each wheel, making them truly one-of-a-kind.
Sold in 8 packs

138264,variable,BontInlineSpeedEclipseskate2pf6061black,,Bont Eclipse Inline Speed Skates 2PF 6061 Black Frame,1,0,visible,"All the performance you loved in the BNT, now with the Bont Eclipse will be even greater stiffness, precision, and refinement.","The Bont Eclipse Boot: Good Fit Right Out of the Box

\nThe Bont Eclipse boot was engineered to solve one of the greatest problems facing skaters: obtaining a perfectly fitting boot that does not need break-in time. The core of this boot is a fully redesigned last that duplicates the natural foot shape. This results in less side pressure, improved arch support, and a comfortable, secure fit around the heel and ankle.
\nSkaters who have attempted the Eclipse have consistently reported that it feels like it was custom-made on the first wear.
\nAnatomical fit with a reengineered last that feels custom-made straight away
\nLightweight, top-quality materials for comfort and performance
\nNarrow, sculpted cuff for a locked-in ankle feel and better control
\nNew sizing system with 5mm steps for accurate online shopping
\nSleek style choices: black, white, or holographic

\nThe Bont Eclipse is lighter than the Jet due to a stiffer resin system and less thermoplastic. Trimming the excess material without compromising a robust carbon base keeps the boot responsive under pressure without bogging you down.
\nWhile being slightly less heat-moldable than the Jet, the Eclipse still has a robust level of customization, maintaining its shape longer and allowing for greater energy transfer when skating.

\nOne of the key upgrades from the Jet is the new cuff design. Some skaters felt the Jet's cuff was too wide and created gaps at the ankle. The Eclipse corrects this with a narrower, contoured design that wraps around the ankle bone for improved comfort and better control, particularly during corners and sprints.

\nThe Bont Eclipse features an overhauled sizing system, abandoning Bont's 50-year-old original sizing. The sizes rise in regular 5mm increments, making it simpler to locate a precise match. This contemporary method better enhances online shopping too, enabling skaters to easily find the ideal boot even when they fall between sizes.

\nThe Bont Eclipse is available in black, white, or holographic, a carefully chosen palette that blends style and functionality. Reduced color choices mean improved factory stock and quicker shipping, and each color works well with the boot's aggressive, race-orientated design.
\nThe Bont Eclipse inline speed skate is perfect for:
\nCompetitive skaters who need a high-performance boot without a fully customized boot
\nAnyone seeking a responsive, lightweight boot with a contemporary look
\nSkaters who value a precise fit and easier sizing
\nWhether you’re stepping up from your first skate or upgrading for better comfort and performance, the Eclipse delivers elite-level performance at an accessible price.

\nSince 1975, Bont has emphasized fit, comfort, and performance in all skate boots. The Eclipse combines decades of expertise and input from thousands of skaters around the globe. It's not merely a new model—it's the next generation of speed skating boots, where ideal fit, exceptional performance, and stylish, edgy style come together.
\nMade to order: about 2 weeks to make
\nSome boots will be held in inventory in Florida; others will be shipped from Asia

\nIf shipping from Asia, delivery will take 2–4 weeks.
